  "name": "milestone-m0-from-docs-state-20260415-0217",
  "idea": "Milestone M0 from docs/state_management_refactor_plan.md \u2014 render telemetry + baseline.\n\nGoal: stand up dev-only render instrumentation and capture baseline render counts for the most important visual surfaces before any architectural refactor begins. Without this baseline, every subsequent milestone's claim \"we reduced renders by X%\" is unfalsifiable.\n\n## Deliverables\n\n1. `src/shared/dev/useRenderBudget.ts` \u2014 a React hook:\n   - Signature: `useRenderBudget(name: string, budget: number)` \u2192 void.\n   - Tracks renders per mount via a ref, increments on each render.\n   - On exceeding budget within an interaction window (default: 1 second since last reset), fires `console.warn('[RenderBudget] <name> rendered <count> times (budget <budget>)')`.\n   - Resets count after a 1-second idle period (no renders for 1s).\n   - Entire hook body wrapped in `if (import.meta.env.DEV)` so production build tree-shakes it. The return is `void` so callers don't need to handle undefined.\n   - Must be a no-op in production \u2014 verify by checking final bundle doesn't contain the string \"RenderBudget\".\n\n2. `src/shared/dev/RenderTelemetryOverlay.tsx` \u2014 a floating dev-only widget:\n   - Bottom-right corner, fixed position, z-index high enough to overlay everything.\n   - Shows a list of instrumented component names + current render count + budget status (green if under, red if over).\n   - Toggleable via a keybind (Ctrl+Shift+R is fine; whatever's not already bound).\n   - Hidden by default; stored-open preference in localStorage.\n   - Only mounted in dev (`if (import.meta.env.DEV)`).\n   - Mount it in `src/app/App.tsx` or the root layout so it sees all render events app-wide.\n\n3. Instrumentation \u2014 call `useRenderBudget(name, budget)` at the top of these components. Confirm names against the repo first (some names may differ from this list; grep if unsure, and halt if a component name can't be found):\n   - `ImageLightbox` (in `src/domains/media-lightbox/ImageLightbox.tsx`) \u2014 budget 5.\n   - `EditModePanel` (in `src/domains/media-lightbox/components/EditModePanel.tsx`) \u2014 budget 3.\n   - `LightboxShell` (in `src/domains/media-lightbox/components/LightboxShell.tsx`) \u2014 budget 5.\n   - `TimelineCanvas` (in `src/tools/video-editor/components/TimelineEditor/TimelineCanvas.tsx`) \u2014 budget 3.\n   - The timeline clip/row component \u2014 grep for it (`ClipRow` was referenced in an earlier draft but does not exist in this repo; find the real component that renders a single clip/track row and instrument it). Budget 2.\n   - `MediaGalleryItem` (in `src/shared/components/MediaGalleryItem.tsx`) \u2014 budget 3.\n   - `TasksPane` (in `src/features/tasks/components/TasksPane/TasksPane.tsx`) \u2014 budget 5.\n   - `ShotsPanelContent` (in `src/features/editor/components/ShotsPanelContent.tsx`, NOT `ShotsPane`) \u2014 budget 5.\n   - `GenerationsPaneGallery` (in `src/features/gallery/components/GenerationsPane/components/GenerationsPaneGallery.tsx`) \u2014 budget 5.\n   - `PreviewPanel` (in `src/tools/video-editor/components/PreviewPanel/PreviewPanel.tsx`) \u2014 budget 5.\n\n   Budgets above are starting heuristics. Confirm each is reasonable by running the dev build after instrumentation and observing actual counts during normal interactions \u2014 adjust budgets UP to real-world + 1 if the observed count is higher than the heuristic (so M0 doesn't ship with perpetual warnings for baseline behavior).\n\n4. `docs/state_management_refactor_baselines.md` \u2014 a new doc capturing measured baseline counts. Structure:\n\n   ```\n   # State Management Refactor \u2014 Baseline Render Counts\n\n   Captured on <date> via useRenderBudget telemetry on commit <sha>.\n\n   ## Per-component baselines\n\n   | Component | Mount | Lightbox open | Clip select | Pane toggle |\n   |---|---|---|---|---|\n   | ImageLightbox | N | N | - | - |\n   | EditModePanel | N | N | - | - |\n   | ...\n\n   ## Interaction sequences\n\n   ### Opening image lightbox in video editor\n   1. <component> rendered X times\n   2. ...\n\n   ### Selecting a timeline clip\n   ...\n   ```\n\n   Minimum 3 interactions captured per applicable component. Numbers recorded should be from a production-built dev server (not HMR-affected) to avoid noise.\n\n## Repo conventions (from reigh-app/CLAUDE.md)\n\n- Prefer editing existing files; don't create unnecessary new files. The two new files above (`useRenderBudget.ts`, `RenderTelemetryOverlay.tsx`) are justified; any additional files require explicit justification.\n- No hardcoded colors \u2014 use Tailwind theme tokens (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`, etc.) in the overlay.\n- Tests only where the hook/widget behavior needs unit coverage \u2014 don't over-test.\n- Don't touch anything outside `src/shared/dev/`, `src/app/App.tsx`, `docs/`, and the specific files being instrumented.\n- Don't modify any edge function, supabase migration, or worker-orchestrator code.\n\n## Gate criteria (for the human reviewer)\n\n- `npx tsc --noEmit` clean.\n- `npm test` matches baseline pass count.\n- Production build succeeds: `npm run build` \u2014 and the final bundle under `dist/` does not contain the string `RenderBudget` or `RenderTelemetryOverlay` (grep the built assets).\n- Baseline doc committed with at minimum 5 components \u00d7 3 interactions measured.\n- Overlay toggle works in dev build; warnings fire when a synthetic burst exceeds a budget.\n\n## Branch\n\n`megaplan/m0-render-telemetry` off `main`. One commit or a small series. PR opened on push.\n\n## Out of scope\n\n- Do not refactor any consumer to reduce renders. This milestone is observation only.\n- Do not install Zustand or introduce any store. That's M1.\n- Do not touch `ImageLightbox`'s component composition beyond inserting `useRenderBudget` at the top.\n- Do not fix any rendering bugs discovered during instrumentation \u2014 note them in the baseline doc as observations.",
